# Legacy `.agents` compatibility

When instructions, notes, or scripts mention paths under `.agents/`, treat them as legacy aliases.

Use these `.cursor/` equivalents by default:

- `.agents/skills/...` -> **`.cursor/claude/skills/...`** (repo `.agents/skills` was consolidated into the Claude bundle tree; some skills are also mirrored under **`.cursor/skills/...`**)
- `.agents/<name>.md` -> `.cursor/agents/<name>.md`
- `.claude/commands/...` -> **`.cursor/commands/...`** (Cursor wrappers) and **`.cursor/claude/commands/...`** (Claude Code bundle inside `.cursor/`); see `claude-commands-cursor-parity.mdc`
- Repo-root **`.claude/`** can be removed after confirming **`.cursor/claude/`** contains the same bundle

Migration policy:

1. Prefer adding or updating files under `.cursor/` only.
2. Do not overwrite existing `.cursor/` files unless explicitly requested.
3. Keep behavior additive and backward-compatible.
